      "content": "The goal is always neatness, regardless of texture; messy hair suggests a lack of control, which is unprofessional. For textured hair, it must be meticulously shaped and kept out of the face, perhaps with a sharp fade or a very controlled style. Straight hair should be slicked back or neatly parted, never looking windblown or overly casual. The key is discipline—whatever the natural texture, it needs to look deliberately managed, not like it was just rolled out of bed.",
